   <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="diagnosis">
      <p>
Diagnosis
</p>
      <p>
Males of this group resemble those of the 
<tp:taxon-name>
silhavyi
</tp:taxon-name>
group by the apophysis at the base of the embolus, but differ by presenting an apophysis at the base of the embolus that is short and conical (
Fig. 12B–C
); the sperm ducts are ‘U-shaped’ in the male palp when it is not expanded (
Figs 9B
, 
10C
). The females can be recognized by the short atrium, presenting a septum or not, and copulatory ducts narrow (
Figs 10F–G
, 
11F
, 
15F–G
).
</p>
   </tp:treatment-sec>
